---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="The 5 Amazon Tasks You Should Automate First — AgentleConsulting Blog"
  description="Not all automation is equal. These five workflows deliver the biggest ROI for the least setup effort."
  ogImage="/blog/og-automation-priority.png">

  <article class="bg-cream">
    <div class="container-site max-w-3xl py-20 md:py-28">
      <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-sage hover:text-sage-dark mb-8 transition-colors">
        ← Back to Blog
      </a>

      <header class="mb-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 bg-sage/10 text-sage rounded-full">Guide</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-slate/40">2026-03-28 · 6 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-heading font-extrabold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-slate leading-tight mb-6">
          The 5 Amazon Tasks You Should Automate First
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate/60 leading-relaxed">
          Not all automation is equal. These five workflows deliver the biggest ROI for the least setup effort — based on 30+ client implementations.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate/75">
        <p>
          One of the most common mistakes we see: sellers try to automate everything at once. They spend three months building a sophisticated system, get halfway through, lose momentum, and end up with half-tested workflows that half-work.
        </p>
        <p>
          The better approach is surgical. Automate the highest-frequency, highest-effort tasks first. Get those right. Then expand. Here's the priority order we recommend based on what we've seen deliver results fastest.
        </p>

        <h2>#1: Post-Purchase Review Requests</h2>
        <p>
          Review requests are the single highest-leverage automation for Amazon sellers. A well-timed, compliant review request can double your review velocity without you lifting a finger.
        </p>
        <p>
          The automation: after an order ships, trigger a follow-up email at day 7 (or day 4 for FBM). Include the "Request a Review" button via Amazon's built-in mechanism — never send buyers off-platform.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sage font-semibold">Typical ROI: +30–60% review rate within 60 days</p>

        <h2>#2: Inventory Repricing</h2>
        <p>
          If you're manually checking competitor prices and adjusting yours, you're not just wasting time — you're losing the buy box and leaving margin on the table.
        </p>
        <p>
          Automated repricing monitors your competitors continuously and adjusts within seconds of a price change. You set the floor; the system protects it.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sage font-semibold">Typical ROI: 5–15% margin improvement within 30 days</p>

        <h2>#3: Order Processing and Confirmation Emails</h2>
        <p>
          Every order that comes in needs to be routed to your warehouse, your accounting system, and your customer. Doing this manually for 50+ orders a day is a full-time job.
        </p>
        <p>
          Automated order processing routes the data to the right place instantly — eliminating the delay between sale and fulfillment that causes customer complaints.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sage font-semibold">Typical ROI: 2–4 hours/day recovered</p>

        <h2>#4: Inventory Restock Alerts</h2>
        <p>
          Running out of stock on a high-velocity SKU is one of the most expensive mistakes in e-commerce. It kills your BSR, your momentum, and your credibility.
        </p>
        <p>
          Automated restock alerts notify you — and optionally your supplier — when inventory drops below your threshold. Some sellers also auto-trigger purchase orders to their supplier.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sage font-semibold">Typical ROI: Eliminates stockout-related BSR drops</p>

        <h2>#5: Financial Reporting Consolidation</h2>
        <p>
          Amazon's native reporting is comprehensive but fragmented. Storage fees, referral fees, FBA costs, advertising spend — they're all in different dashboards.
        </p>
        <p>
          Automated daily consolidation pulls everything into one view so you know your true margin every morning. No more end-of-month surprises.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sage font-semibold">Typical ROI: Early detection of margin erosion worth thousands per quarter</p>

        <div class="bg-sage/5 border border-sage/20 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-sage mb-2">Where to Start?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate/70">
            If you're not sure which of these applies to your business most urgently, <a href="/contact" class="underline">book a free 20-minute call</a>. We'll give you a straight answer on your highest-ROI automation priority in the first call — no sales pitch.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-stone">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between flex-wrap gap-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-sage/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="font-heading font-bold text-sage text-sm">AC</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-sm text-slate">AgentleConsulting</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate/40">Automation Engineering Team</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary text-sm py-2.5 px-5">Talk to Us →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
